WEBVTT

00:43.874 --> 00:45.176
Welcome to the Well Community Church.

00:45.236 --> 00:52.607
So glad you're hanging out with us here today for those of course joining us here in our Clovis Auditorium to those online and our Student Center venue outside Fig Garden.

00:52.627 --> 00:55.972
We've got people all over, just so grateful to share the time with you.

00:55.992 --> 00:57.674
If we have not met yet, my name's Brad.

00:58.095 --> 01:01.941
One of the pastors here, I get the privilege of handling God's word with us this week.

01:01.961 --> 01:05.045
We are in a very interesting sort of season here at the Well.

01:05.065 --> 01:11.795
We're doing a four week series and cultivates sort of sharing some of the next steps of what we think the Lord is leading us into.

01:11.815 --> 01:13.618
We've handed out a brochure over the last

01:13.794 --> 01:19.662
A couple of weeks, if you did not get one, maybe worth grabbing, just to give you a little bit of the details as to what is coming next.

01:19.702 --> 01:22.185
We'll cover that more in detail here next week.

01:22.225 --> 01:26.971
But before we got to the what, we thought we'd take a couple of weeks and just sort of talk through the why.

01:27.191 --> 01:31.677
Here a couple of weeks ago, we talked about the importance of reaching the next generation.

01:32.178 --> 01:41.650
That what we're doing here is really not just for us, though certainly we want to strengthen this generation, but our heart is to create something that generations from now,

01:41.826 --> 01:48.272
sort of sown some seeds or planted trees, if you will, for their benefit as well, that they might experience the gospel also.

01:49.113 --> 01:56.340
Last week, we talked a little bit about the purpose of a church, being a place of teaching and training and equipping and discipling.

01:56.801 --> 02:01.385
We reminded one another that really it's not the role of a church to entertain.

02:01.466 --> 02:05.930
We're really not here to provide ministries, per se, that meet our needs.

02:06.711 --> 02:10.034
We're here to teach, train, equip and disciple that we might walk

02:10.242 --> 02:11.924
more intimately with Jesus.

02:12.444 --> 02:18.069
And as we saw the growth of the early church, we saw that the bigger the church got, the more they focused on that purpose.

02:18.510 --> 02:26.277
What we'd like to cover this week is what does it mean for us as followers of Jesus to partner with God by way of personal generosity?

02:26.337 --> 02:30.021
Now, as we get into this subject matter, there is no question.

02:30.501 --> 02:35.907
Acknowledgement, the elephant in the room, that had you known it was a message on giving, many of you would have chosen to stay home.

02:36.867 --> 02:39.570
And to be honest, I don't blame you.

02:40.034 --> 02:42.478
It's not because of what the Bible says.

02:43.059 --> 02:44.200
It's because of what we've seen.

02:44.821 --> 02:49.889
And some of you have seen some things or experienced some things that are not biblical whatsoever.

02:50.230 --> 02:54.957
You've seen shady pastors who stood up and fleece to congregation for their own personal gain.

02:55.037 --> 03:04.191
You saw church leaders that mismanaged finances or misappropriated finances or just skimmed money off the top for themselves.

03:04.792 --> 03:08.498
And in that, of course, that put a bad taste in your mouth as it should.

03:08.962 --> 03:10.283
But I want you to think about it this way.

03:11.304 --> 03:18.131
If giving or personal generosity is a mark of spiritual maturity and we choose not to do so because of what we've seen.

03:19.252 --> 03:26.099
What happens if we, because somebody mishandled the word of God if we quit reading our Bible?

03:26.820 --> 03:32.785
What happens if we ever go to a church gathering and it got a little weird that we say, you know what, I'm not going to church anymore?

03:33.446 --> 03:37.490
Or if we quit praying or worshiping or serving or living in community,

03:37.602 --> 03:39.705
simply because something weird happened.

03:40.305 --> 03:43.189
The reality is something weird is always gonna happen.

03:43.769 --> 03:53.281
And yet that doesn't mean we jettison or disregard our participation in what the Word of God invites us to be a part of for God's glory and our good.

03:53.301 --> 03:57.446
And so what I'd really like to do if we can is rewrite the narrative.

03:57.927 --> 04:03.954
And I'd like to just walk through candidly what does the Bible say and what does it not say about the issue of personal

04:04.034 --> 04:09.340
Generosity and what is our responsibility and opportunity to partner with God?

04:09.380 --> 04:10.982
And that's where this whole journey begins.

04:11.082 --> 04:16.529
Before we can talk about personal generosity, we need to recognize the nature and character of our God.

04:16.789 --> 04:19.472
Our God is a generous God.

04:19.492 --> 04:31.186
When you read through the creation account and you see in the first two chapters of Genesis, God speaks the world into existence, forms it by the word of his mouth, shapes Adam and Eve from the dust of the earth,

04:31.362 --> 04:35.809
And in chapter one, verse 16 says he makes the stars also as if an afterthought.

04:36.029 --> 04:38.753
We have to ask the question, why did God do that?

04:39.694 --> 04:44.161
God who is preexisting and is fully satisfied in and of himself had need of nothing.

04:44.782 --> 04:46.364
He did not create for himself.

04:46.945 --> 04:50.431
He did not create half dome for him or the sierras for him.

04:50.491 --> 04:53.735
He didn't create the beautiful sunset over the Pacific for him.

04:53.796 --> 05:00.786
He actually did it for us because God is a generous God and his creation is an act of generosity.

05:01.186 --> 05:03.630
But thankfully it doesn't simply stop there.

05:03.650 --> 05:07.596
In fact, Psalm 104, 24 says, oh Lord, how many are your works?

05:08.277 --> 05:09.719
And wisdom you have made them.

05:10.060 --> 05:12.123
The earth is full of your possessions.

05:12.163 --> 05:14.887
That God by His grace created something beautiful for us.

05:15.788 --> 05:19.755
And even in His generosity was moved to redeem us.

05:20.456 --> 05:23.961
Because as you read through your Bible, something terrible happens in Genesis chapter three.

05:23.981 --> 05:29.810
It's a passage we circle around to often here at the well, because it's where sin comes into the world.

05:30.210 --> 05:32.994
And what we find is Adam and Eve rebel against God.

05:33.955 --> 05:37.620
And several things are passed on to them and therefore passed on to us.

05:38.100 --> 05:40.643
They inherit death both spiritually and physically.

05:41.284 --> 05:44.568
They inherit shame and guilt which they seek to cover and hide.

05:45.349 --> 05:48.333
They inherit corruption where the image of God is defaced.

05:49.074 --> 05:50.076
Something's not right.

05:51.077 --> 05:53.660
And in that they are separated from God.

05:54.321 --> 05:56.444
And then finally they inherit autonomy.

05:56.724 --> 05:58.226
And autonomy is the

05:58.786 --> 06:03.611
innate desire that we all have to do life on our own alone and without God.

06:03.951 --> 06:08.215
And yet, God by His grace, because He loved us, He gave.

06:08.535 --> 06:15.202
God so loved the world that He gave His only begotten Son, that whoever believes in Him would not perish but have everlasting life.

06:15.242 --> 06:16.463
Because God is a generous God.

06:16.483 --> 06:18.085
He didn't leave us in our sin.

06:18.145 --> 06:20.767
He didn't leave us in spiritual and physical death.

06:20.787 --> 06:22.889
He didn't leave us in autonomy.

06:22.909 --> 06:25.332
In fact, God by His grace gave Jesus for us.

06:25.712 --> 06:27.634
He was under no obligation to do so.

06:28.098 --> 06:36.387
God would be no less holy and no less loving had He left us in our sin, but by His grace He was moved on our behalf.

06:36.427 --> 06:45.937
In fact, Ephesians 2 tells us that God being rich and mercy because of His great love with which He loved us while we were dead and our transgressions made us alive together with Christ.

06:46.017 --> 06:51.644
And the goal of the gospel is to reorient us back into right relationship with Him.

06:51.664 --> 06:57.650
That it's not simply that when we trust in Jesus Christ, we snap God into our already busy life.

06:58.178 --> 07:02.563
No, in fact, the Bible's gonna go as far as to say that we have been crucified with Christ.

07:02.623 --> 07:04.666
It's no longer we who lives, it's Christ who lives in us.

07:05.327 --> 07:11.134
That if we've embraced the gospel of Jesus Christ, we have died and our life is hidden with Christ in God.

07:11.634 --> 07:18.943
In fact, Paul tells the Church of Corinth, he says, for the love of Christ controls us, having concluded this, that one died for all and therefore all died.

07:19.003 --> 07:24.950
And he died for all so that we who live may no longer live for ourselves, but for him who died.

07:25.511 --> 07:28.114
Which means then, because of sin, we were in

07:28.386 --> 07:39.743
autonomy, but God by His grace has saved us that we might now reflect His image more accurately, that we might be generous as our God by His very nature is generous.

07:39.823 --> 07:44.490
But we need to acknowledge this tension, that generosity is unnatural.

07:45.151 --> 07:57.970
Because even though we are in Christ, we still have the presence of flesh, which means it's still possible for us to operate in selfishness, not generosity, in a sense of mine, not in a sense of His.

07:58.626 --> 08:07.096
And so in fact, in Galatians 5, 17, Paul's gonna remind us that the flesh sets its desire against the spirit and the spirit against the flesh.

08:07.116 --> 08:13.024
These are in opposition to one another, which simply means your Christian life is not going to be easy.

08:13.925 --> 08:25.058
There is gonna be this sense of clash and what generosity can be for us is a dashboard light to show you, am I operating in flesh or am I operating in spirit and generosity?

08:25.459 --> 08:28.242
Maybe the thing that tips your hand as to which you're operating.

08:28.354 --> 08:38.484
And that's possibly why Jesus is going to speak in the gospel accounts more on money than any subject matter other than the kingdom of God.

08:38.504 --> 08:43.188
In fact, there is more in our Bible about money than heaven and hell combined.

08:43.208 --> 08:49.094
11 of the 29 parables include teaching on money.

08:49.715 --> 08:51.817
There are 500 verses on prayer.

08:52.297 --> 08:52.978
Wow, that's a lot.

08:52.998 --> 08:54.559
Prayer seems to be pretty important.

08:54.960 --> 08:57.362
There are over 2,000 on the issue of money.

08:57.954 --> 08:58.335
Why?

08:58.355 --> 09:02.002
Because I think it's an indicator of what's happening on the inside.

09:02.022 --> 09:11.781
And what I'd like to do is walk through just some general observations from the Bible regarding this issue and then we'll finish by getting into some practical next steps.

09:11.801 --> 09:16.290
If you are looking for passages, there are two that we're going to comment on more in-depth and other.

09:16.370 --> 09:18.194
Second Corinthians chapter 9.

09:18.498 --> 09:27.132
And first Timothy chapter six, we'll get there here eventually, but we are gonna skip our rock rather through most of our Bible, pulling up some concepts.

09:27.152 --> 09:35.245
Here's a first observation, that whatever we have, we have been entrusted by God.

09:35.405 --> 09:38.730
So whatever we have has been entrusted to us by God.

09:38.790 --> 09:43.738
Psalm 127 says, unless the Lord build the house, they labor in vain who build it.

09:44.639 --> 09:46.322
And unless the Lord guard the city,

09:46.466 --> 09:47.948
The watchman keeps awake in vain.

09:47.968 --> 09:55.520
It's a vain thing to stay a plate, to rise up early, or to eat the bread of painful labor for the Lord gives to his beloved, even while they sleep.

09:55.580 --> 09:58.945
Whatever we have has been entrusted to us by God.

09:59.005 --> 10:04.794
In fact, in Matthew chapter 25, Jesus gives a wonderful parable called the parable of the talents.

10:04.854 --> 10:06.296
We'll walk through it if you want to turn there.

10:06.817 --> 10:08.559
We'll spend a little bit of time there as well.

10:08.639 --> 10:12.004
Matthew 25, starting verse 14, the parable of the talents.

10:12.024 --> 10:13.106
Let's know what Jesus says.

10:13.826 --> 10:15.409
He says, for it is just like a man.

10:15.429 --> 10:17.372
He's speaking about life in his kingdom.

10:18.113 --> 10:25.264
For it, life in his kingdom is just like a man who goes out on a journey, calls his slaves together, and entrusts his possessions to them.

10:26.066 --> 10:38.466
And then in Matthew 25 verse 15, he says, to one, he gave five talents, to another he gave two, and to another one, and each according to their own ability, and then he went on his journey.

10:39.748 --> 10:41.170
Immediately the one who received

10:41.346 --> 10:44.009
five talents traded and made five more.

10:44.690 --> 10:48.695
Verse 17, in the same manner, the one who had two talents gained two more.

10:48.895 --> 10:52.940
Now the question you're probably asking is what's a talent?

10:52.960 --> 10:58.006
Well, we lose a little bit of impact on this passage because we assume that's some sort of ability.

10:58.466 --> 11:00.348
But a talent was a unit of measurement.

11:00.949 --> 11:05.594
So it'd be like saying he gave one guy five pounds and another guy two pounds and another guy a pound.

11:06.255 --> 11:08.658
Which begs the second question, well, a pound of what?

11:09.218 --> 11:12.281
I mean, a pound of rocks very different than a pound of gold, for example.

11:12.701 --> 11:16.645
And we don't know explicitly what the unit of measurement is here.

11:16.725 --> 11:20.969
We don't know what the object is that they're measuring, but verse 18 gives us an indication.

11:21.770 --> 11:24.432
It says, the one who had received one talent, he went away.

11:24.472 --> 11:28.957
He dug a hole in the ground and he hid his master's money.

11:29.577 --> 11:33.881
That word money literally is translated from silver coins.

11:34.542 --> 11:38.706
So whatever this parable the talents is about, it's about some monetary

11:38.946 --> 11:43.833
unit that was given to them, five, two, and one respectively.

11:43.853 --> 11:49.401
And then of course in verse 19, this master now comes home and settles accounts with them.

11:49.621 --> 11:57.332
What's interesting about the parable of the talents is they are given varying amounts depending on their own verse 15 ability.

11:58.153 --> 12:02.519
Some people were entrusted with more, some with less, some with less still.

12:02.960 --> 12:07.506
All of them were entrusted, whatever the Lord thought they needed and could handle.

12:07.618 --> 12:13.066
at that moment, whether it was a lot or whether it was little, which leads to the second observation.

12:13.487 --> 12:16.993
We are called to be content with whatever we've been entrusted.

12:17.874 --> 12:20.318
Now, that's not to suggest that we don't hustle.

12:20.498 --> 12:25.045
That's not to suggest you can't pick up an extra shift because Christmas gifts are expensive.

12:25.466 --> 12:34.179
It's not to suggest that the labor is not worthy of its wage, but what it does mean is that we're called to be content with whatever he's entrusted to us.

12:34.199 --> 12:36.082
There was a survey done some years ago

12:36.258 --> 12:43.231
And they interviewed people who made 30k a year asking them what would they need in order to be satisfied?

12:43.952 --> 12:45.074
And the answer was 60.

12:45.975 --> 12:51.205
So they interviewed people who made 60k a year and said, what would you need in order to be satisfied?

12:51.766 --> 12:52.708
And they said 100.

12:53.549 --> 12:55.352
So they interviewed people who made 100k a year.

12:55.412 --> 12:56.214
What would you need?

12:56.695 --> 12:57.376
And they said 500.

12:57.436 --> 12:58.578
You see where this is going.

12:58.978 --> 13:00.460
500 said we need a million.

13:00.600 --> 13:02.743
People who made a million said we need five million.

13:02.903 --> 13:09.492
The reality was it didn't matter which group or demographic that they interviewed, what would it take for them to be satisfied?

13:09.512 --> 13:10.774
It was all the same thing.

13:10.834 --> 13:11.936
What was it?

13:11.956 --> 13:12.256
More.

13:12.897 --> 13:16.923
And that's the thing about discontentment in what God has entrusted to us.

13:17.463 --> 13:19.726
We set our sights on accumulating more.

13:20.127 --> 13:26.235
How many of you have gotten, by the way, in the last 10 years, a raise, only a couple months later to forget that you even got it?

13:27.117 --> 13:28.178
I don't know what happened.

13:28.322 --> 13:30.004
Like did my bills rise as well?

13:30.444 --> 13:36.692
Because when you set your sights on the accumulation of more, it's like a bird with wings and it just kind of flies away.

13:37.313 --> 13:40.857
And so to be content with whatever he has given us is the goal.

13:40.897 --> 13:46.824
Now it's interesting, in Philippians 4, 13, probably the most over quoted and misunderstood passage in all of your Bible.

13:47.344 --> 13:50.488
It says, for I can do all things through Christ who strengthens me.

13:51.169 --> 13:52.410
And we all go, that's right, amen.

13:52.430 --> 13:53.932
I'm gonna run the two cities marathon.

13:53.952 --> 13:55.634
I can do all things through Christ.

13:56.194 --> 13:57.595
I'm going to hike Mount Everest.

13:57.675 --> 13:59.357
I can do all things through Christ.

14:00.158 --> 14:02.120
That's not what that passage is about at all.

14:02.821 --> 14:09.908
In fact, that passage, if you look at the context of Philippians 4 in the previous verses, it's about contentment.

14:10.308 --> 14:12.550
Listen to what Paul says, Philippians 4, 11.

14:13.071 --> 14:18.737
He says, not that I speak from want, for I have learned to be content in whatever circumstances I'm in.

14:19.477 --> 14:21.499
I know how to get along with humble means.

14:22.240 --> 14:24.082
I also know how to live in prosperity.

14:24.450 --> 14:32.418
In any and every circumstances, I have learned the secret of being filled and of going hungry, of having an abundance and of suffering need.

14:32.618 --> 14:35.701
I can do all things through Christ who strengthens me."

14:35.721 --> 14:39.064
So that passage has nothing to do with human attainment whatsoever.

14:39.084 --> 14:44.830
It has everything to do with our perspective by way of contentment of whatever it is God has entrusted to us.

14:44.890 --> 14:48.433
And I love that He says, I have learned the secret of contentment.

14:48.493 --> 14:48.693
Why?

14:48.713 --> 14:49.975
Because it's unnatural.

14:50.575 --> 14:53.618
And it requires us to retrain in life with Him.

14:54.242 --> 14:56.205
And by the way, it's not that money is evil.

14:56.245 --> 14:56.866
Don't miss hear that.

14:56.906 --> 14:58.508
The Bible never says money is evil.

14:58.809 --> 15:05.498
There's this false Christian narrative that has come from earlier in church history that somehow godliness meant poverty.

15:06.319 --> 15:07.761
There's nothing wrong with having money.

15:07.801 --> 15:11.927
If God has given you a gift of money, we'll get into that first Timothy 6 in just a little bit.

15:12.208 --> 15:17.034
There's nothing wrong with it, but the love of money, Paul says, is the root of all sorts of evil.

15:17.395 --> 15:22.322
It's the longing for it, which leads us to the third observation, that we are wealthy

15:23.170 --> 15:26.695
Compared to the rest of the world, whether you knew it or not.

15:27.376 --> 15:28.237
Now, I'll give you an example.

15:28.738 --> 15:30.220
Size is also relative.

15:30.400 --> 15:32.583
I am a relatively large dude.

15:33.304 --> 15:36.508
Most rooms I walk into, I'm one of, if not the largest guy there.

15:36.528 --> 15:37.269
Bigger's not better.

15:37.409 --> 15:39.472
It's just a reality, okay?

15:39.492 --> 15:42.416
But I went and did a chapel for an NFL football team.

15:42.436 --> 15:44.579
I did a chapel for the Ravens some years ago.

15:45.340 --> 15:47.703
And I realized very quickly, size is relative.

15:48.464 --> 15:52.530
Because I walked in and these guys were absolutely massive.

15:52.674 --> 15:55.817
And I'm looking at these, this crowd, a guy, like a punter was bigger than I was.

15:56.197 --> 15:59.000
And I'm thinking, every guy here looks like he could hurt me.

15:59.320 --> 16:01.362
And you just realize it is all relative.

16:01.843 --> 16:03.485
Wealth is similar in that.

16:04.405 --> 16:09.030
We tend to look around and think, oh, you know, this person's got more than me and this person's got more than me.

16:09.050 --> 16:10.732
But we're looking in the wrong direction.

16:11.272 --> 16:21.522
See, when it comes to a global perspective of wealth, if you make more than 35,000 a year, you're in the top 1% of income earners in the world.

16:21.954 --> 16:25.718
If you have clothing choices, you are considered wealthy.

16:26.459 --> 16:30.383
If you have food choices, you are considered wealthy.

16:31.244 --> 16:34.227
If you have a vehicle to drive, you are wealthy.

16:34.307 --> 16:39.493
If you have an option of vehicles to drive, you are exceedingly wealthy.

16:40.014 --> 16:46.741
In fact, 80% of humanity makes less than $10 a day, or the equivalent of about $4,000 a year.

16:47.582 --> 16:48.523
So are you wealthy?

16:49.564 --> 16:51.346
Probably.

16:51.522 --> 16:56.190
the world in general, yes, you probably are, which leads me to the fourth observation.

16:56.250 --> 17:01.059
Therefore, we are called to be stewards of whatever we've been entrusted.

17:01.119 --> 17:03.383
We are not owners.

17:03.403 --> 17:12.018
Now, before we embraced the gospel, we were in the flesh, which meant we were in autonomy, which made sense then that we thought it was our car.

17:12.642 --> 17:19.192
and our clothes, and our food, and our money, and our house, or apartment, or dorm room, or whatever.

17:19.492 --> 17:20.374
We thought it was ours.

17:20.594 --> 17:21.876
But then we embraced the gospel.

17:22.637 --> 17:24.440
And since we embraced the gospel, we died.

17:24.480 --> 17:25.642
We've been crucified with Christ.

17:25.662 --> 17:26.563
It's no longer we who lives.

17:26.603 --> 17:27.044
It's Christ.

17:27.344 --> 17:28.866
Now we realize it's actually not mine.

17:28.886 --> 17:29.287
It's His.

17:29.868 --> 17:31.751
The Lord owns the cattle on a thousand hills.

17:32.031 --> 17:41.906
The earth is the Lord's in all it contains, which means then by His grace, those cattle on a thousand hills, He took some to auction and gave some of the money for you and I that we might have it in our accounts.

17:42.306 --> 17:46.372
But it's not ours, it's his, which means then we are stewards.

17:47.513 --> 17:51.699
And Jesus speaks about this issue of what do we do then as stewards?

17:51.719 --> 18:02.133
Stewards are one who manages someone else's money, which simply means we recognize that it's not ours, it's his, and therefore we should put it to use where he would want it to be used.

18:02.193 --> 18:04.517
Jesus put it this way in Matthew six.

18:04.537 --> 18:08.402
He says, do not store it for yourself treasures on earth where moth and rust destroy.

18:08.866 --> 18:19.661
or where thieves break in and steal, but store it for yourself treasures in heaven, or neither moth nor rust destroy, or neither thieves break in and steal, for where your treasure is, there your heart will be also.

18:19.701 --> 18:20.782
We are stewards.

18:21.383 --> 18:22.144
We are not owners.

18:22.224 --> 18:23.286
Fifth observation.

18:23.306 --> 18:29.895
Therefore, as stewards, we are invited to invest what resources we have into kingdom initiatives.

18:30.736 --> 18:32.098
Kingdom initiatives.

18:32.118 --> 18:35.643
Every investor, by the way, is looking for a return on your investment.

18:36.163 --> 18:38.226
You could put it in a bank, make a little money,

18:38.434 --> 18:43.600
on interest, you can get involved with this or that, make a little bit more money, but everybody's wanting to know, what's my ROI?

18:44.060 --> 18:47.544
Well, when it comes to being stewards, it's a kingdom ROI.

18:48.124 --> 18:59.056
It's not the same, which means we're investing our resources into gospel initiatives, kingdom initiatives, so that we might see fruit or a return on that investment spiritually.

18:59.076 --> 19:01.299
Well, what did it look like in our Bibles?

19:01.379 --> 19:08.146
Well, in your Old Testament, you had men and women responsible now for supporting the work of what was called the House of God.

19:08.546 --> 19:19.158
and that changed throughout your Old Testament, it started as a tabernacle grew into the temple, but you gave what you called a tenth of what you had, a tenth meaning of tithe.

19:19.238 --> 19:22.962
Now when I say the word tithe, some of you get hives, stay with me for a moment, okay?

19:23.743 --> 19:29.690
Because all the tithe was was a benchmark in your Old Testament of what you would give to support the house of God.

19:29.710 --> 19:36.978
And so if you were a great farmer, you'd take the first tenth of what your harvest was, and you would give that into the tabernacle or the temple.

19:37.410 --> 19:42.438
And you did so, so you could support now the operation of the house of God.

19:42.458 --> 19:44.321
But you also gave what was called offerings.

19:44.922 --> 19:49.729
And offerings, if you read through the book of Leviticus, by the way, where most Bible reading plans go to die.

19:50.451 --> 20:05.394
In the first several chapters, it's sin offering, peace offering, love offering, wave offering, all these offerings given, which come out if you do the math to about 25% of someone's income, which means the tithe and the offerings came out to be about 35%.

20:05.474 --> 20:09.098
of what you made, and why would you give that in your Old Testament?

20:09.118 --> 20:18.029
Well, it reinforced your dependence upon God by giving, you were reminding yourself and your community, God is the one who richly supplies.

20:18.109 --> 20:31.826
It also supported the ministry, the ongoing work of the temple and the tabernacle, and it also supported the religious feasts and festivals that took place there, and then finally it reinforced the spiritual priority of God in the midst of the people.

20:32.387 --> 20:34.930
But what about in the New Testament?

20:35.042 --> 20:36.604
invited to do in the New Testament.

20:36.644 --> 20:42.773
Well, we are also invited to give, to reinforce our spiritual dependence upon God, who richly supplies our needs.

20:43.373 --> 20:50.383
We are also invited to support the various ministries, not of the Old Testament, Tabernacle or Temple, but in the New Testament, a church.

20:51.044 --> 21:01.458
We are also invited to support the various ministries of the church, like things that happening in our gatherings, our midweek ministries, our Monday night recovery ministry, middle school stuff, high school stuff, et cetera.

21:01.826 --> 21:07.913
And then we were also invited to give to reinforce the spiritual priority of God in our midst as well.

21:07.953 --> 21:12.918
But the question is how much are we called by God to give?

21:13.458 --> 21:14.780
And that's an interesting question.

21:15.260 --> 21:16.902
And the answer is, well, it kind of depends.

21:17.823 --> 21:23.569
Where your Old Testament gave a clear 10%, your New Testament takes another tact, another direction.

21:23.890 --> 21:25.571
Turn to 2 Corinthians chapter 9.

21:27.173 --> 21:31.698
In 2 Corinthians chapter 9, the Apostle Paul, of course, riding to the Church of Corinth, which was

21:32.002 --> 21:36.668
arguably the wealthiest city at that time, maybe second only to Rome.

21:37.129 --> 21:38.430
They didn't simply have a port.

21:38.450 --> 21:39.351
They had two ports.

21:39.652 --> 21:42.696
They were ridiculously wealthy by way of trade.

21:42.856 --> 21:49.224
And in 2 Corinthians 9, a church had been started there, and he's talking to them in chapters eight and nine about personal generosity.

21:49.244 --> 21:50.205
But listen to what he says.

21:51.687 --> 21:55.512
He says, now this I say, by way of principle, 2 Corinthians 9, 6.

21:56.113 --> 21:58.356
The one who sows sparingly will reap sparingly.

21:58.376 --> 22:00.338
The one who sows bountifully will reap

22:00.610 --> 22:01.251
bountifully.

22:01.271 --> 22:11.666
There's a principle when it comes to kingdom, our allies, that when you hold what God gives you with the closed hand, don't be surprised if he doesn't continue to fill that closed hand.

22:11.686 --> 22:17.794
But if you can begin to learn to open that hand and support things that God once supported, don't be surprised if he blesses you.

22:17.815 --> 22:20.418
Now, this isn't prosperity gospel.

22:20.979 --> 22:24.484
This isn't saying, if I sow a seed into this ministry, I can buy a jet.

22:24.504 --> 22:25.906
That's not what this is saying.

22:26.498 --> 22:36.028
What it is saying though is by way of principle, if I'm an open hand and I give, God may give to me, press down and shake it over that I can continue to partner with him in generosity.

22:36.068 --> 22:37.610
But what's interesting to me is verse seven.

22:38.691 --> 22:40.113
How much should you give?

22:40.453 --> 22:43.236
Are we called by God to give a 10% tithe?

22:43.396 --> 22:44.197
I don't think so.

22:44.598 --> 22:54.388
If you look at verse seven, he says, each one must do just as he is purposed in his heart, not grudgingly or under compulsion for God loves a cheerful giver.

22:55.289 --> 22:56.050
Well, what does that mean?

22:56.578 --> 23:01.125
That means you should give whatever you feel joy giving.

23:01.946 --> 23:03.568
And if it's 10%, great.

23:03.789 --> 23:05.892
And if it's not, then give less.

23:06.953 --> 23:07.935
Which brings the point up.

23:08.135 --> 23:09.958
Well, what if you don't feel good about giving at all?

23:10.138 --> 23:11.500
Well, then don't give at all.

23:13.523 --> 23:15.526
If you can't give with joy, don't give.

23:16.507 --> 23:17.168
And pray about it.

23:17.288 --> 23:19.231
And see what God does in your heart.

23:19.251 --> 23:21.074
Because what's most important is

23:21.154 --> 23:27.201
if where your treasure is, there your heart is, how we participate with God financially is an indication of the heart.

23:27.441 --> 23:31.806
If you're not comfortable giving with joy, the issues not your giving, the issues your heart.

23:32.447 --> 23:35.270
So just go to the Lord with that and see what he begins to do.

23:35.330 --> 23:36.271
Now here's the thing.

23:37.332 --> 23:40.276
Are we as followers of Jesus called to give?

23:41.037 --> 23:42.839
Well the answer is yes, and let me frame it this way.

23:43.399 --> 23:45.502
As a follower of Jesus, are we called to read our Bible?

23:46.303 --> 23:47.884
Yeah, are we called to pray?

23:48.906 --> 23:49.266
Yeah.

23:49.442 --> 23:51.765
Are we called to attend a church gathering?

23:52.326 --> 23:52.566
Yeah.

23:53.067 --> 23:54.469
Are we called to live in community?

23:54.870 --> 23:55.110
Yeah.

23:55.490 --> 23:56.432
Are we called to give?

23:57.373 --> 23:57.613
Yeah.

23:59.075 --> 24:01.098
Why would we treat one different from the others?

24:02.120 --> 24:08.689
And again, just because something bad happened somewhere doesn't mean that we quit participating with God in our giving.

24:08.909 --> 24:18.162
Now, if 10% is a good baseline and in some ways it is, consider now our participation in generosity

24:18.498 --> 24:21.342
as something a little bit broader than just the tithe.

24:21.462 --> 24:24.386
Turn to 1 Timothy 6, 1 Timothy 6.

24:25.408 --> 24:37.665
Paul writing to one of the other wealthy cities in your New Testament, the city of Ephesus, Timothy being the pastor, and he's writing to the wealthy there and encouraging them with how to steward their riches.

24:37.865 --> 24:46.738
In verse 17, he says, instruct those, this is 1 Timothy 6, 17, instruct those who are rich in this present world

24:47.138 --> 24:51.304
not to be conceited or to fix their hope on the uncertainty of riches.

24:51.364 --> 24:57.713
Now, have you ever met somebody like that who is arrogant and conceited because of their wealth?

24:58.454 --> 25:01.038
Wealthy doesn't mean you're better, all right?

25:01.058 --> 25:02.700
Which means poverty doesn't mean you're worse.

25:03.462 --> 25:09.330
It just means some of you are five talent people and some of you are one talent people and God's going to entrust you with whatever.

25:09.506 --> 25:19.683
He feels like you can handle, and he says here, don't fix your hope now on the uncertainty of riches, but rather, fix your hope on God who richly supplies you with all things to enjoy.

25:19.703 --> 25:24.230
It was an interesting phenomenon years past.

25:24.250 --> 25:27.335
I may have said this already, but if not here, or if so, here it is again.

25:27.896 --> 25:36.370
That somehow poverty was better, that godly people were poor, that if you weren't destitute, poor, living in, you know, squalor, that you weren't

25:36.546 --> 25:37.648
You weren't necessarily godly.

25:37.948 --> 25:38.809
And I don't think that's true.

25:38.829 --> 25:43.596
He clearly doesn't say, he says it's not true here, which means he has given you all things to richly enjoy.

25:43.717 --> 25:47.522
Is it wrong for those of you who have the capacity to make money?

25:47.783 --> 25:49.325
Is it wrong for you to go on vacation?

25:49.605 --> 25:49.826
No.

25:50.507 --> 25:52.349
Is it wrong for you to drive a really nice car?

25:52.630 --> 25:52.810
No.

25:53.371 --> 25:55.794
Is it wrong for you to travel the world?

25:56.195 --> 25:56.455
No.

25:56.976 --> 26:04.247
If God has blessed you and you are able to do those things, he's given you all things to richly enjoy, but don't miss verse 18.

26:05.208 --> 26:06.450
He says, instruct them.

26:06.754 --> 26:12.901
to do good, to be rich in good works, to be generous and ready to share.

26:12.921 --> 26:15.423
If you can do both, go get it.

26:16.304 --> 26:17.746
Get your passport and go.

26:18.467 --> 26:23.392
But don't forget, verse 18 is about a kingdom ROI.

26:24.193 --> 26:32.362
And in so doing, you're storing up verse 19 treasures for yourself of the good foundation for the future so that you may take hold of that, which is life indeed.

26:32.742 --> 26:36.466
Which means if God has given you the ability to be generous and

26:36.674 --> 26:39.779
enjoy some things, then by all means, do that.

26:40.239 --> 26:43.845
All right, let me give you a couple of maybe principles if you wanted to get started.

26:43.905 --> 26:50.895
If you said, okay, look, I'm listening, I'm interested, I've not really thought much about how to participate in terms of personal generosity.

26:50.915 --> 26:51.917
Where do I even begin?

26:52.117 --> 27:03.314
All right, first, pray about it, because this is between you and the Lord, and just see what God has for you, and see where He might want you to begin, and see what it might look like for you,

27:03.426 --> 27:07.711
to begin to participate financially, however you feel led to give.

27:07.831 --> 27:13.818
Second, however you participate financially, one of the encouragements would be biblically, give systematically.

27:14.538 --> 27:15.459
Give systematically.

27:15.479 --> 27:16.000
And here's why.

27:16.481 --> 27:20.966
In your Old Testament, they gave an an agrarian calendar according to whatever they harvested.

27:21.506 --> 27:27.413
In the New Testament, that shifted a little bit so that offerings were gathered every week when the church assembled.

27:28.134 --> 27:32.018
But giving systematically, that frequency reminds you

27:32.130 --> 27:34.714
What I have is given to me, my God, I'm called to be a steward.

27:34.734 --> 27:36.196
I want to invest in kingdom things.

27:36.536 --> 27:39.901
And so whatever that means, systematically for you to do that.

27:40.001 --> 27:42.965
Some of you get paid certain times, you know, in the month.

27:42.985 --> 27:51.797
Some of you get paid commissions, whatever it means, but systematically is helpful because remember your participation and generosity is a sign of spiritual maturity.

27:51.817 --> 27:55.141
It's like a spiritual discipline that we participate in with God.

27:55.242 --> 27:58.546
Third, give proportionately, give proportionately.

27:58.978 --> 27:59.639
What does that mean?

27:59.719 --> 28:02.764
Well, again, summer five, summer two, summer one talent people.

28:02.804 --> 28:05.829
I don't know what your net worth is, but give proportionately.

28:06.309 --> 28:11.117
For some college students, a 10% tithe might be way out of reach.

28:11.758 --> 28:14.442
We've got college students working at Uncle Harry's.

28:15.143 --> 28:17.226
They're not gonna be able to give maybe 10%.

28:18.368 --> 28:22.835
But for some folks who are established in their career, 10% might be too low.

28:23.336 --> 28:27.282
And you get to pray about that with the Lord, and whatever that is for you,

28:27.458 --> 28:28.920
It's to be given with joy.

28:29.220 --> 28:30.362
So give proportionately.

28:31.283 --> 28:33.065
Fourth, give sacrificially.

28:33.906 --> 28:40.855
Jesus in Mark chapter 12 gives us a wonderful picture of contrast of a man of means who gives that of a surplus.

28:40.875 --> 28:44.980
And then a woman who comes in and gives of her pennies, her of all that she had.

28:45.480 --> 28:51.127
And that widow's might is commended because it's really not equal gifts, it's equal sacrifice.

28:51.308 --> 28:53.330
And what happens is this woman gave

28:53.506 --> 29:00.252
All that she had, it showed her commitment to the Lord, versus the other guy who could cut a check, and so he did, that really meant nothing to him.

29:00.453 --> 29:04.797
When we give, it should have an impact on our life a little bit.

29:05.477 --> 29:11.603
I mean, it shouldn't put us in the poor house, but you should feel it a little bit, because what that does is say, Lord, I trust you.

29:12.144 --> 29:16.688
You're a guy who provides, and I'm gonna give, and I wanna see what you wanna do in return.

29:16.768 --> 29:20.592
And then five, if you're gonna give, give secretly, give secretly.

29:22.533 --> 29:23.154
You don't need to,

29:23.906 --> 29:26.629
Put it on Instagram, all right, nobody needs to know.

29:27.190 --> 29:29.773
You don't need to tell your neighbor, it's really none of their business.

29:29.813 --> 29:40.064
In fact, Jesus says, when you give to the poor, don't let your left hand, pardon me, know what your right hand is doing, which means just give secretly, it's between you and the Lord.

29:40.104 --> 29:44.129
And then sixth, whatever you give, as we've said already, give with joy.

29:45.030 --> 29:48.594
In Exodus 25 to Moses tells the people of God,

29:49.026 --> 29:55.737
to come bring their contributions to the Lord, every man whose heart moves him, you shall raise a contribution.

29:56.318 --> 30:03.590
And as I've said, if you can't give with joy, then the biblical, I think, admonition would be, well, then don't give.

30:04.351 --> 30:08.097
And that's a terrible thing to say if you're trying to raise money.

30:08.278 --> 30:11.203
We're not trying to raise money, we're trying to cultivate hearts.

30:12.024 --> 30:14.208
And so if you can't give with joy, then don't.

30:14.368 --> 30:15.730
And the seventh and final thing,

30:16.098 --> 30:24.587
The biblical picture seems to be you tithe to your local church and you give offerings to causes or non-profits that are involved with areas of passion.

30:25.168 --> 30:31.315
Because remember in your Old Testament, it was the tabernacle and the temple that was supported, the New Testament, it seems to be the local church.

30:32.456 --> 30:34.779
And so you give to whatever church, by the way, you call home.

30:35.499 --> 30:40.124
The well is a unique place because we have a lot of people that will come and we're kind of a side hustle for them.

30:40.185 --> 30:43.188
They attend another church, but they come, check us out.

30:43.208 --> 30:45.170
I go, great, serve their give there.

30:45.250 --> 30:46.231
bring your Bible here.

30:46.732 --> 30:49.295
And if we can help train and equip you, then that's great.

30:49.395 --> 30:54.922
But whatever place is feeding you spiritually, that's the place that we need to begin to contribute to.

30:55.002 --> 31:00.729
Now, one of the things that's unique about the well is that we are a non-denominational church.

31:01.229 --> 31:04.093
And all that means is there is no cavalry that's coming.

31:04.813 --> 31:08.017
We have no corporate headquarters that can give us any resources.

31:08.077 --> 31:11.922
We have no other funding sources for over two decades.

31:12.034 --> 31:19.183
We've been helping people connect to God and to each other in every neighborhood because people have said, I believe in what's happening and I want to participate.

31:19.243 --> 31:22.808
And God by His grace has been faithful to resource what He's called.

31:23.449 --> 31:25.191
And some of you may say, okay, well, I'm interested.

31:25.231 --> 31:26.573
I might want to begin to give here.

31:26.953 --> 31:27.934
How do I even give?

31:28.655 --> 31:30.998
Well, you'll notice we don't pass a plate.

31:31.018 --> 31:32.180
We don't pass an offering plate.

31:32.200 --> 31:36.125
We don't do it on purpose because some of you here are guests and I want to talk to you in just a moment.

31:36.786 --> 31:40.050
I don't want you feeling awkward when the offering plate comes and you're like,

31:41.058 --> 31:42.280
Is this like, give one, take one?

31:42.300 --> 31:43.462
Like, what do I do with this?

31:44.403 --> 31:46.707
And so we just prefer not to pass a plate.

31:46.727 --> 31:51.154
But if you do want to participate financially here at the well, you can give online.

31:51.434 --> 31:53.397
Our website's got a give page you can go to.

31:54.239 --> 31:57.003
You can bring gifts in here if you want.

31:57.023 --> 32:01.610
There's two give boxes at the back of every auditorium and every campus in gathering.

32:01.630 --> 32:04.595
And then if you'd like, you could even, if you're old school, you can mail it in.

32:04.655 --> 32:05.216
Totally fine.

32:05.596 --> 32:06.618
Mailing into our office.

32:06.999 --> 32:09.202
We'd be happy to accommodate you in that regard.

32:09.890 --> 32:12.534
And some of you are like, yeah, I need a little more information.

32:13.075 --> 32:14.737
I want to know what your internal controls are.

32:14.777 --> 32:15.899
I want to know what your audit said.

32:16.760 --> 32:17.561
No problem at all.

32:17.662 --> 32:18.443
Go to our give page.

32:18.463 --> 32:19.745
We have a financial piece there.

32:20.105 --> 32:23.550
We are happy to share with you anything and everything that you need.

32:23.570 --> 32:31.642
We do a self-imposed audit every year simply to make sure we handle every dime that comes in with the highest standards financially possible.

32:31.662 --> 32:32.784
And we'd love to share that with you.

32:33.365 --> 32:35.568
But to the guests who are here, I mentioned you a little bit.

32:36.449 --> 32:39.634
I really want you to know we are not interested in your money.

32:39.746 --> 32:41.529
we're interested in your heart.

32:41.549 --> 32:48.259
So this message in some ways to the guest is maybe not for you because we're wanting to show you what Christians do.

32:48.799 --> 32:54.868
So we do baptisms and we do, we'll enjoy communion together, we'll have people share their stories.

32:54.888 --> 32:56.371
That's what Christians do.

32:56.491 --> 32:57.312
We want you to see that.

32:57.452 --> 33:00.757
Christians also are invited to participate in generosity.

33:00.797 --> 33:03.301
But for you, if you're a guest, keep bringing your Bible.

33:03.401 --> 33:06.866
And when the day comes, that you say, hey, I trust this place and I want to

33:06.946 --> 33:09.149
I wanna steward what resources God has given to us.

33:09.550 --> 33:10.772
We'd be happy to help you with that.

33:11.232 --> 33:15.519
But there are a number of you who are new to the well, but this is home for you now.

33:15.979 --> 33:18.223
We'd love to invite you to participate with us.

33:18.463 --> 33:34.066
And in fact, I would say as we continue to grow as a church, we are gonna need everyone to prayerfully consider what our individual participation may be, whether it be much or whether it be little, but we wanna invite you into that and then to the well family.

33:34.754 --> 33:37.397
It is just the privilege to be a part of a generous church.

33:38.058 --> 33:52.216
This church for years, God is so faithfully resourced what he has called because people understand that our participation with God by way of generosity is an expression of what the gospel has done in our hearts and it's been awesome to be a part of that together.

33:52.696 --> 33:55.360
As I close, I just wanna close with a little bit of a benediction.

33:55.400 --> 34:00.226
Just something to kind of wrap our time together and then I'll pray and we'll wrap up here.

34:00.246 --> 34:03.730
It says this, may our generous God continue to lead us

34:04.162 --> 34:09.228
as we seek to faithfully steward what he has entrusted to us with joy.

34:09.269 --> 34:22.966
And my hope as we walk through the message here this week is that we might, by God's grace, reframe what generosity could look like with no guilt and no shame and no obligation, but simply invitation to participate.

34:23.367 --> 34:25.529
However, God leads you with joy, amen?

34:26.190 --> 34:26.931
Let's pray.

34:26.951 --> 34:32.338
Father, we're grateful for the work of the gospel, for the kingdom, our eyes that we have been experiencing,

34:32.770 --> 34:36.194
over two decades and for the work that is still yet before us.

34:37.316 --> 34:44.124
As we seek to be faithful to your word, even in defiance of culture, even in rewriting old experiences.

34:44.645 --> 34:49.551
Lord, we want to be faithful to your word as a community that stewards well, what you've entrusted to us.

34:49.591 --> 34:54.417
So thank you for the opportunity together to be a part of what you're doing in our great city.

34:54.457 --> 35:01.266
Bless us, I pray, and as we pray about our own participation by way of personal generosity, would you lead us however you see fit

35:01.570 --> 35:02.722
and we'll thank you for the journey.

35:02.965 --> 35:04.562
In Jesus' name, amen.

